        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 3:31PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 331 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Tilton to Chattoogaville. These storms were
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Frequent cloud to ground lightning and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Lightning is one of nature's leading killers. If you can
hear thunder, you are close enough to be struck by
lightning. Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding
especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Dalton, Summerville, Trion, Resaca, Lyerly, Subligna, Suttles Mill,
Tidings, Lake Marvin, Tilton, Mill Creek, Villanow, Berryton,
Chattoogaville, Sugar Valley, Everett Springs, James H. Floyd State
Park, Holland, and Armuchee.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.  Electrical
appliances should not be used unless in an emergency. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
